        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 11:58PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 1157 PM EDT/1057 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Campbellsville, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Campbellsville, Knifley, Taylor County Airport, Feathersburg, Coburg,
South Campbellsville, Romine, Casey Creek, Elk Horn, and Acton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
